<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
In version 2.2.7 this skill is the one and only thing that helps you with wands and staves. Race/subrace/class/level don't matter anymore. <p>
If you're annoyed with the high fail rate of your stick despite level 50 in magic device, the only thing you can do is get a stick with a better level range(i.e. Wand of Tidal Wave [5 34] instead of Wand of Tidal Wave [1 20]) so you start at a lower fail rate which you can improve more with maximum skill. 
</p>
<p>
Rods, <a href="./artifact">artifact</a>s, and misc <a class="nonexistent" href="./Junkarts">Junkarts</a> such as "the Gem of Knowledge" are supposed to improve with the old <a class="interwiki" title="Self" href="./RogueLike/Angband"><img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/moin-inter.png" alt="[Self]" height="16" width="16">Angband</a> "magic device" ability; which appears to improve with magic device skill. In 2.3 only the magic device skill is supposed to influence the magic device ability, so they are essentially a duplicate. 
</p>
<p>
It is not possible to have a zero or even a "decent" fail rate on some mid- or high-level sticks(i.e. mid-level wand tidal wave); the game is meant that way. Many players pray for longer casting times rather than 60% fail rates; but fail rates are the way it's implemented... 
</p>
</div><div id="footer">


